metadata.name: Artificialmente Natural #17
metadata.description:
"Artificialmente Natural" is an abstract, natural collection where lines are utilized to create a pseudo-representation of natural colors and textures.

One of my main inspirations comes from my father, who currently lives in Germany. He is always sending beautiful pictures of nature in every season of the year, but especially his latest pics from spring were truly inspiring and thought-provoking. There are 15 palettes representing each season in different ways, but also, some more surrealistic pallettes could appear. Either way, thank you dad, we may live oceans apart but you're still a huge influence in my life.

metadata.name: The beauty of imperfection #12
metadata.description:
Drawing shapes repeatedly, spinning and rotating. I use basic shapes like square, rectangle, and triangle to create this art. Regular shapes are perfect but it's a little bit boring, so I make them imperfect, just like "hand drawing". I also tried to make this generative art great for physical print, so that I can hang it on the wall. Here we go.

5 background colors:
Black, White, Blue, Green, and Red

Press “space” to play animation.
Press “s” to save.

Made with p5js.
Created by Costa C. | OneRocket.nft

metadata.name: Altered #106
metadata.description:
Adj. Changed in character or composition, typically in a comparatively small but significant way.

Please note that the display is progressive and can take some time to finalize.

Artwork by Patrice Orenes-Lerma - @patxol - 2022
Made with math, love & p5js.
CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Features include :

- 20 color palettes (10 standard, 10 rare)
- 8 palette progression types
- 3 aspect ratio (Portrait is standard, 1:1 and landscape are rare)
- 8 Alteration types
- 3 Alteration power levels
- 5 types of symmetry
- 3 densities
- Spaced mode and Sharp mode

metadata.name: Shattered Moons #240
metadata.description:
🌘🌗🌖Shattered Moons🌔🌓🌒

Explore deep space moons through this pure SVG generative experiment.

Features:
- Striped Background
- Shadows
- Vapors
- Horizontal Vapors
- Meteors
- Colored Meteors
- White Moon (0.5%)

SVG being a vectorial format, this work can be displayed/printed at any size.
Press 's' on Live View to save the SVG.
Press 'p' on Live View using a Chromium based browser to export as PNG.

Also, to fully enjoy your piece, I'd suggest to use a Chromium based browser as the SVG renderer gives more details.
